File: As many as 1 in 3 people are dating online and approximately 57 percent of online daters have admitted to being dishonest. WEEKEND CONTENT JOHANNESBURG - Research suggests that concerns around online dating are warranted. According to a report by international anti-virus firm Kaspersky, as many as one in three people are dating online. Approximately 57 percent of online daters have admitted to being dishonest and about 55 percent have experienced some sort of threat or problem while dating online. * 1st for Women Insurance offers these tips and guidelines that can make your online dating experience a safe one. Made with Visme Infographic Maker